Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
reportVtInstCount(25.10)                              reportVtInstCount(25.10)

Name
       reportVtInstCount  -  Reports  the  instance distribution across the VT
       partitions in the design

Syntax
       reportVtInstCount

       [-help]

       [-area]

       [-detailed]

       [-leakage]

       [-outFile <fileName>]

       Reports the instance distribution across the VT partitions in  the  de-
       sign.  By  default, the Innovus software partitions the design into ei-
       ther two or three VT buckets. Each library, cell,  and  instance  falls
       into one of these buckets and is reported by this command.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation  for each reportVtInstCount parameter. For a detailed de-
              scription of the command and all of its parameters, use the  man
              command:

              man reportVtInstCount

       -area  Prints  the  area information across libraries in each VT parti-
              tion.

       -detailed
              Prints complete details in the specified file.

              Note: Before specifying this parameter,  you  must  specify  the
              file name using the -outFile parameter.

       -leakage
              Prints  the leakage distribution across the libraries in each VT
              partition. When you specify this parameter, a  complete  leakage
              power  analysis is performed on the design, which takes a little
              long to run.

       -outFile <fileName>
              Prints the output in the specified file in the  format  required
              for user-defined VT partitioning.

              Note:  To  print  the same report that is output to the log that
              includes all leakage and instance information, specify the  -de-
              tailed parameter. If you do not specify the -detailed parameter,
              the -outFile parameter will only print the VT partitions.

Examples
              * The  following  command  outputs the Vt partitions to the file
                VT_Partitions.rpt:

                reportVtInstCount -outFile Vt_Partitions.rpt

                The Vt_Partitions.rpt file contains the following information:

              * The following commands output the Vt distribution as  well  as
                information  in  instances  and cells. When the output file is
                not specified, the reportVtInstCount command outputs  only  to
                the log. The second command outputs both to the log and to the
                output file.

                reportVtInstCount

                reportVtInstCount -detailed -outFile VT_detailed.rpt

                The report will contain the following information:

              *

                The  following  command outputs the Vt distribution as well as
                the area distribution across libraries in each VT partition:

                reportVtInstCount -area

                The report will contain the following information:

              *

                The following commands output reports with the  leakage  power
                numbers  included.  The first command outputs only to the log.
                The second command outputs both to the log and to  the  output
                file.

                reportVtInstCount -leakage

                reportVtInstCount    -leakage    -detailed   -outFile   VT_de-
                tailed_leakage.rpt

